# Fog of War: Technical API Specification (v1.0.0)

This document provides a detailed, OpenAPI-style specification for the Fog of War backend services. It covers authentication, real-time game state streaming via gRPC, and action-based RPCs for gRPC-Web clients.

## 1. Connection Information

| Protocol | Purpose | Endpoint |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **gRPC (HTTP/2)** | Native clients / High performance | `localhost:50051` (Local & Internal to Render deployment) |
| **gRPC-Web (HTTP/1.1)** | Browser-based clients (Vite/React) | `localhost:8080` (Local) |
| **gRPC-Web (HTTP/1.1)** | Browser-based clients (Vite/React) | `https://fog-of-war-v4y8.onrender.com` (Deployed Public URL) |

---

## 2. Authentication & Security

The API uses **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** for authorization. All requests except `Login` must include the token in the gRPC metadata (headers).

- **Header Key**: `authorization`
- **Scheme**: `Bearer <token>`
- **Token Claims**: `player_id` (UUID)

---

## 3. Service: `AuthService`

The gateway for onboarding players via Solana wallet signatures.

### `rpc Login(LoginRequest) returns (LoginResponse)`
Authenticates a user and returns an access token.

**Request Schema (`LoginRequest`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `public_key` | `string` | Base58 encoded Solana public key. |
| `signature` | `string` | Signature of the `message` signed by the user's wallet. |
| `message` | `string` | The plain text message that was signed (e.g., "auth_me"). |

**Response Schema (`LoginResponse`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `access_token` | `string` | JWT token to be used in subsequent requests. |
| `player_id` | `string` | Unique UUID assigned to the player. |

---

## 4. Service: `GameService`

The core gameplay service managing sessions and real-time interactions.

### `rpc Connect(ConnectRequest) returns (stream GameStateUpdate)`
**Type:** Server-side Streaming
Subscribes to the 10Hz authoritative game state broadcast.

**Request Schema (`ConnectRequest`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `game_id` | `string` | UUID of the game session to join. |

**Stream Object (`GameStateUpdate`):**
Sent every 100ms.
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `game_id` | `string` | Contextual game ID. |
| `server_time` | `int64` | Unix timestamp of the tick. |
| `players` | `[]Player` | List of all players in the session. |
| `loot_items` | `[]LootItem`| Visible/available loot on the map. |
| `npcs` | `[]NPC` | Non-player character states. |
| `hazards` | `[]Hazard` | Active traps or environmental dangers. |
| `events` | `[]GameEvent`| Recent discrete events (e.g., "Player A killed Player B"). |

---

### `rpc Move(MoveRequest) returns (MoveResponse)`
**Type:** Unary
Updates the player's intended target destination.

**Request Schema (`MoveRequest`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `game_id` | `string` | Contextual game ID. |
| `target_x` | `float` | Target X coordinate on the 128x128 grid. |
| `target_y` | `float` | Target Y coordinate on the 128x128 grid. |

**Response Schema (`MoveResponse`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `success` | `bool` | True if the target was accepted. |
| `error_message`| `string` | Reason for failure (if applicable). |

---

### `rpc CollectLoot(CollectLootRequest) returns (CollectLootResponse)`
**Type:** Unary
Attempts to collect a loot item. This triggers a confidential verification via **Arcium**.

**Request Schema (`CollectLootRequest`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `game_id` | `string` | Contextual game ID. |
| `loot_id` | `string` | UUID of the loot item to collect. |

**Response Schema (`CollectLootResponse`):**
| Field | Type | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `success` | `bool` | True if Arcium verified the position match. |
| `new_encrypted_balance`| `string`| The player's updated loot balance, encrypted by Arcium. |

